## Ontology Overview

This ontology provides a comprehensive knowledge representation of the Unified NixOS-Only Ash Framework System v6.0.0, defining all entities, relationships, concepts, and behaviors within the system architecture.

### Ontological Foundations

| Foundation | Definition | Scope |
|------------|------------|-------|
| **Entity Classification** | Formal categorization of all system components | Complete system coverage |
| **Relationship Modeling** | Explicit definition of all inter-entity relationships | Full relationship graph |
| **Behavioral Semantics** | Formal specification of system behaviors and interactions | All operational patterns |
| **Conceptual Domains** | Logical grouping of related concepts and entities | Domain-driven organization |
| **Constraint Specification** | Formal definition of system constraints and invariants | Complete rule set |

### Knowledge Representation Principles

1. **Completeness**: Every system component is represented
2. **Consistency**: No contradictory definitions or relationships
3. **Clarity**: Unambiguous entity and relationship definitions
4. **Extensibility**: Framework for future system evolution
5. **Validation**: Formal verification of ontological integrity

